President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Vicki Miles-LaGrange as a Member of the Board of Trustees of the Harry S Truman Scholarship Foundation. Miles-LaGrange is currently the Chief Judge of the United States District Court for the Western District of Oklahoma, a position she has held since 2008. She was the first African-American federal judge in the six states that make up the 10th Circuit. Before becoming a judge, Miles-LaGrange served as the first female U.S. Attorney in Oklahoma and was a member of the Oklahoma State Senate. She has also served as a trustee of Vassar College and Oklahoma City University. She received her B.A. from Vassar College and her J.D. from Howard University School of Law.

President Obama has also announced his intent to appoint James Wright Willis as a Member of the Cultural Property Advisory Committee. Willis is the founder of James Willis Tribal Art in San Francisco and has been in the art business since 1972. He is a member of the San Francisco Art Dealers Association and Friends of Ethnic Art in San Francisco. Willis has been a member of the Cultural Property Advisory Committee since 2003 and has served on the boards of the Museum for African Art, the San Francisco Craft and Folk Art Museum, and the Ancient and Tribal Arts Study Committee of the M. H. De Young Museum. He received his B.A. from Pomona College and his M.A. from San Francisco State.